    "note_sources": [
      {
        "source_file": "notes/harder_batch4_web_compute.md",
        "content": "### EP-92\n- Quick literature check:\n  - The problem page now cites a circle-point incidence consequence giving $f(n)\\ll n^{4/11}$ (via Janzer-Janzer-Methuku-Tardos-type input).\n- Finite compute signal:\n  - Model families (grids, triangular patches, regular polygons) gave finite $f$-values mostly in the low single digits for $n\\le 64$.\n- Interpretation:\n  - Finite models are compatible with subpolynomial ambitions, but too small-scale to discriminate between $n^{o(1)}$ and slower power laws."
      }
    ],
    "script_sources": [
      {
        "source_file": "scripts/harder_batch4_quick_compute.mjs",
        "heading": "finite profiles for f(n)-style local equidistance in model sets.",
        "content": "// EP-92: finite profiles for f(n)-style local equidistance in model sets.\n{\n  const rows = [];\n\n  for (const m of [4, 5, 6, 8]) {\n    const pts = gridPoints(m);\n    const n = pts.length;\n    const f = localEquidistantMin(pts);\n    rows.push({\n      model: 'square_grid',\n      n,\n      f_model: f,\n      f_over_n_pow_4_over_11: Number((f / n ** (4 / 11)).toFixed(6)),\n    });\n  }\n\n  for (const n of [16, 25, 36, 64]) {\n    const pts = triPatchPoints(n);\n    const f = localEquidistantMin(pts);\n    rows.push({\n      model: 'triangular_patch',\n      n,\n      f_model: f,\n      f_over_n_pow_4_over_11: Number((f / n ** (4 / 11)).toFixed(6)),\n    });\n  }\n\n  for (const n of [12, 18, 24, 30]) {\n    const pts = regularPolygon(n, 1, 0);\n    const f = localEquidistantMin(pts);\n    rows.push({\n      model: 'regular_polygon',\n      n,\n      f_model: f,\n      f_over_n_pow_4_over_11: Number((f / n ** (4 / 11)).toFixed(6)),\n    });\n  }\n\n  out.results.ep92 = {\n    description: 'Finite model lower profiles for per-center equidistant multiplicity.',\n    rows,\n  };\n}"
      }
    ],
